From: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 30 Apr 2026 20:56:32 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] drm/panfrost: drop noisy 'Purging X bytes' shrinker print

The pr_info_ratelimited at the tail of panfrost_gem_shrinker_scan fires
every time the shrinker frees pages, which on a 512 MB device with
chromium driving Panfrost is constant. The rate-limit's own 'callbacks
suppressed' summary then prints to console too. Drop the line - the
shrinker is core-path infrastructure, the freed count is already
returned to the caller, and KERN_INFO console spam from a kiosk
runtime is a regression that masks real warnings.

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Upstream-Status: Pending
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/panfrost/panfrost_gem_shrinker.c | 3 ---
 1 file changed, 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/panfrost/panfrost_gem_shrinker.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/panfrost/panfrost_gem_shrinker.c
index 2fe967a90..95dace974 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/panfrost/panfrost_gem_shrinker.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/panfrost/panfrost_gem_shrinker.c
@@ -83,9 +83,6 @@ panfrost_gem_shrinker_scan(struct shrinker *shrinker, struct shrink_control *sc)
 
 	mutex_unlock(&pfdev->shrinker_lock);
 
-	if (freed > 0)
-		pr_info_ratelimited("Purging %lu bytes\n", freed << PAGE_SHIFT);
-
 	return freed;
 }
 
-- 
